Claims CLAIMS  What is claimed is: 1. An automated parking system comprising: parking entrance unit; vehicle transport shuttle; shuttle trail means; plurality of parking locations; and controller, adapted to: establish communication with the vehicle to be parked in the parking system; receive signal from the vehicle indicating that the vehicle is ready to be controlled by the controller; receive signal indicating that the parking system is ready to receive and park the vehicle; control the movement of the vehicle toward loading on the vehicle transport shuttle; control the movement of the vehicle transport shuttle toward a designated parking location; and control the movement of the vehicle toward the designated parking location. 2. The system of claim 1 , the controller is further adapted to: receive indication from the vehicle, after it moved into the designated parking location, indicative of the completion of the parking process; and record the designated parking location as associated with the parked vehicle. 3. The system of claim 1 , wherein the controller is further adapted to: receive a signal indicative of a request to transport a parked vehicle to the parking entrance unit; control the vehicle transport shuttle to arrive and stop in front of the parking location associated with the parked vehicle; 

 control the parked vehicle to move onto the vehicle transport shuttle; control the vehicle transport shuttle to move and stop in front of the parking entrance unit; control the parked vehicle to move to unload off the vehicle transport shuttle and onto the parking entrance unit; and issue a signal indicative that the parked car is ready to be taken out of the parking system. 4. A method for automatically parking a vehicle in a parking system comprising a parking entrance unit, a vehicle transport shuttle, shuttle trail means, plurality of parking locations and a controller, the method comprising: establishing communication with a vehicle to be parked in the parking system; receiving signal from the vehicle indicating that the vehicle is ready to be controlled by the controller; receiving signal from the vehicle indicating that the vehicle is ready to be controlled by the controller; receiving signal indicating that the parking system is ready to receive and park the vehicle; controlling the movement of the vehicle toward loading on the vehicle transport shuttle; controlling the movement of the vehicle transport shuttle toward a designated parking location; and controlling the movement of the vehicle toward the designated parking location. 5. The method of claim 4, further comprising: receiving indication from the vehicle, after it moved into the designated parking location, indicative of the completion of the parking process; and recording the designated parking location as associated with the parked vehicle. 6. The method of claim 4, further comprising: 

